My wittle bug,

Oh how this year has flown. I’m having the hardest time processing that it’s your birthday. One year ago today, mama was labor for about 6 hours before you graced the world with your stoic presence. This year we’ve done so much as a little family and I couldn’t have asked for a better first year with my first babe. Your daddy and I love you more than you will ever know. Your 7 toothy smile and little chats are what makes every minute worth it. Life is full of first’s and I can’t wait to have more with you 💗

Love you so much,

Mama

Tay Appreciation Post:

When @l_fresh and I met, I hated Taylor. I could thank my sorority sisters who all had Love Story as their ringtones for that one. As Logan and I got more invested in each other, my love for Taylor grew because he actually like her lots.

Fast forward to my first concert seeing her, Speak Now, then Red, then 1989, then Rep right before we got married. I have a #fearless tattoo and had a Fearless quote on the wall of my favorite apartment.

Last night was full circle for us. We shared a lot of Taylor during our relationship - we can’t go into a store without hearing one of her songs, Elsie listened to Taylor while in my belly, we announced we were having a girl with Taylor shoes and Elsie was born one day before Taylor’s birthday.

Last night, we both cried as we realized Taylor has been such an important figure in our lives. During #longlive the lyric is “if you have children someday, when they point to the pictures, please tell them my name, tell them how the crowds went wild, tell them how I hope they shine” That was it. @taylorswift we thank you and we love you 💜

Bentley 2009-2023

I’ve had to start and stop this a few times so I could process that he’s actually gone. He was the literal best dog in the entire world; kind words will never be good enough for his Saint-like soul. God put Bentley on this earth,  and in my life, to show me what true love was. I cannot put into words how hard this week has been for me. I got Bentley when I was in college. He loved playing with toys, before Hinckley, and loved giving kisses including to his kitty brothers. He was always by my side or not far from it. He always was human beaning for food and even said please with his toe beans. He was such a good boy and lived the best life. We went on trips, pets allowed or not, and never got caught. Bentley never barked - only sneezed when he needed something. He had more frequent flyer miles than most humans and was perfect every time. He loved to steal socks and give toe kisses. He loved bananas, popcorn and French fries. There will never be another like him, and I will live the rest of my life missing his kisses, snores and love.

I love you Ween. Someday, I will get to hold you again, but until then watch over us and give Nanny Jane my love.

An evening at @enchantchristmas @enchantsanjose is as magical as an evening at the North Pole ☃️

We had a wonderful time partnering with @enchantsanjose @enchantchristmas this holiday season to share our experience at this beautiful event! From the delicious food, creative drinks, glittery lights, spacious family suites and VIP experience to the many instagramable moments, you must go! Tickets are on sale now through Dec 31 where they are having a #NYE party you won’t soon forget ✨

❕TIPS❕

✨Family friendly but select an EARLY entry time! Less people, shorter lines and less stroller traffic

✨Walk around the perimeter of the park to enjoy lots of cute photo ops, shopping and food vendors

✨Standing under the snow is a MUST

✨ Dress warm as there aren’t any heaters throughout - but that’s to be expected

✨ Stroller friendly for kids who need a break

✨Enjoy one beautiful, festive evening
